  "title": "Baby Measurements",
  "difficulty": "Moderate",
  "question_text": "<div class=\"paragraph\">After a baby is born, doctors take routine measurements of three different statistics: height, weight, and head size. A pediatrician wonders if there is a linear association between height and head size. She collects data from the next <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$20$</span> babies she examines and finds a correlation of <span class=\"tex2jax_process\">$0.82$</span>. </div><div class=\"paragraph\">Interpret this value in the context of this problem.</div>",
  "image_files": [],
  "choices": [
    {
      "letter": "A",
      "text": "When height goes up by\n1\n, the head size increases by approximately\n0.82\n."
    },
    {
      "letter": "B",
      "text": "When height equals\n0\n, the head size is approximately\n0.82\n."
    },
    {
      "letter": "C",
      "text": "82\n%\nof the variation in height is accounted for by the least-squares regression line of height and head size."
    },
    {
      "letter": "D",
      "text": "There is a strong, positive, linear association between height and head size."
    },
    {
      "letter": "E",
      "text": "The correlation is\n0.82\ninches."
    }
  ],
  "correct_answer": "<strong>Choice 'D'</strong> is the correct answer. ",
